242
00:11:25,401 --> 00:11:28,598
So by comparison,
Sam's patient's done nothing wrong.

243
00:11:28,738 --> 00:11:31,366
What 17-year-old hasn't wanted to sleep
with one of his teachers?

244
00:11:31,507 --> 00:11:34,442
Donna was in a position of power,
and she abused that.

245
00:11:34,577 --> 00:11:36,511
Why assume
a 17-year-old isn't mature enough?

246
00:11:36,645 --> 00:11:38,579
Because he's being forced
to grow up too quickly.

247
00:11:38,714 --> 00:11:41,842
To make decisions about his life
that he's just not ready to make.

248
00:11:41,984 --> 00:11:43,315
Think about yourself at 17.

249
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:48,253
I was mature, all right? Heather wasn't.
But thank you, Naomi, for the free therapy.

250
00:11:50,526 --> 00:11:54,121
All right, if this were Maya
and a 35-year-old male gym teacher...

251
00:11:54,263 --> 00:11:56,322
Well, I would kill him.
But that's not the...

252
00:11:56,465 --> 00:11:59,628
I know that there's a double standard here,
but it's different when it's a girl.

253
00:11:59,769 --> 00:12:00,895
- It is.
- It shouldn't be.

254
00:12:01,036 --> 00:12:02,833
SAM:
Look, I hate abuse.

255
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:05,099
But I don't think
that's what we're dealing with here.

256
00:12:05,241 --> 00:12:06,606
Donna is not a criminal.

257
00:12:06,742 --> 00:12:08,801
Now, as long
as she doesn't see him again,

258
00:12:08,944 --> 00:12:11,344
that's all we want, isn't it?

259
00:12:13,382 --> 00:12:16,909
Even if she gets the new heart,
he won't look after her.

260
00:12:17,052 --> 00:12:19,316
- He's not gonna take care of her.
- Phillip?

261
00:12:19,455 --> 00:12:22,515
He sends me in his place.
Who does that?

262
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:25,183
Even now,
he's in the lobby on his BlackBerry.

263
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:27,955
This is his baby. His wife.

264
00:12:28,097 --> 00:12:29,792
He should be here for her, you know?

265
00:12:30,266 --> 00:12:33,394
There still isn't a heart,
but Janine is at the top of the list.

266
00:12:33,536 --> 00:12:35,902
I've also got a call in
to the head of UNOS.

267
00:12:36,038 --> 00:12:37,471
Janine's blood type O, so am I.

268
00:12:37,606 --> 00:12:39,870
It's the most common.
It shouldn't be so hard.

269
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:43,240
That works in her favor,
but organ donation is a difficult process.

270
00:12:43,379 --> 00:12:45,939
- Supply can't meet the demand.
- I wanna do something.

271
00:12:46,449 --> 00:12:48,474
If I could give her my heart...

272
00:12:48,617 --> 00:12:50,107
We're gonna find you one.

273
00:12:50,252 --> 00:12:54,484
How long do Janine and the baby have
to find a heart before they die?

274
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:57,922
Forty-eight hours.

275
00:13:09,138 --> 00:13:10,503
Isn't that someone else's job?

276
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:12,539
I can't stop. Nesting.

277
00:13:12,675 --> 00:13:14,870
I see mess or clutter
or things out of place and...

278
00:13:17,313 --> 00:13:20,749
So she seems nice.

279
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:22,475
Lisa. And her kid is cute.

280
00:13:22,618 --> 00:13:24,313
Yeah, I like them.

281
00:13:25,855 --> 00:13:27,652
What? What's wrong?

282
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:31,692
I just hate it that you're maybe
carrying my baby and I didn't tell her.

283
00:13:31,827 --> 00:13:33,920
- You think you should?
- You think I shouldn't?

284
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,497
It's just... You're happy.

285
00:13:36,632 --> 00:13:37,929
And I'm all for full disclosure,

286
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:41,696
but do you think you should tell her
something before there's anything to tell?

287
00:13:41,837 --> 00:13:43,270
SHELDON:
Violet.

288
00:13:45,274 --> 00:13:48,402
Oh, sorry, Pete.
Were you two in the middle of a?

289
00:13:48,544 --> 00:13:49,909
Just finishing.

290
00:13:53,716 --> 00:13:55,877
- Are those for me?
- No, for me.

291
00:13:56,018 --> 00:13:59,215
From a patient. She's in love with me.

292
00:14:00,756 --> 00:14:02,724
Her name is Anita.

293
00:14:02,858 --> 00:14:05,918
I started treating her a few months ago.
She was painfully shy.

294
00:14:06,061 --> 00:14:07,756
She wanted me to help her
be more assertive

295
00:14:07,897 --> 00:14:10,297
with a co-worker
she had fallen in love with.

296
00:14:10,432 --> 00:14:12,866
She didn't know how to talk to him.

297
00:14:13,002 --> 00:14:15,266
And as she realized
how easy it was to talk to you,

298
00:14:15,404 --> 00:14:16,803
she channeled her love to you.

299
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:18,907
- It's classic transference.
- Clearly.

300
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:21,669
- You don't have to say it like that.
- Like what?

301
00:14:21,810 --> 00:14:25,473
Like a woman couldn't fall in love with me
unless it was a therapeutic mistake.

302
00:14:25,614 --> 00:14:29,550
- I didn't say that.
- I can be very charming, you know.

303
00:14:29,685 --> 00:14:30,879
- I know.
- Well...

304
00:14:31,020 --> 00:14:36,219
I was just saying that it happens,
that it's part of the process.

305
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,753
Are you having your own feelings?

306
00:14:38,894 --> 00:14:42,261
This is not about counter-transference.

307
00:14:42,398 --> 00:14:47,392
I mean, granted my love life
is at best complicated right now,

308
00:14:47,536 --> 00:14:50,004
but I just wanted to talk to a colleague.

309
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:51,970
I guess, go on record if nothing else.

310
00:14:52,107 --> 00:14:57,238
But also to see if you had any secrets.

311
00:14:57,379 --> 00:14:58,903
[SIGHS]

312
00:14:59,615 --> 00:15:01,640
I hate to fail.

313
00:15:02,451 --> 00:15:06,148
I think you won't fail.

314
00:15:06,522 --> 00:15:08,854
She's lucky to have you, Sheldon.

315
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:17,260
And can you really blame her?

316
00:15:23,072 --> 00:15:24,539
[CHUCKLES]

317
00:15:26,308 --> 00:15:31,336
Dell, I'm going out, so if my 2:00 gets here
before I do, put her in a room for me.

318
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,607
Yeah, what else would I do?

319
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:37,582
Dell, later we're gonna have a talk.

320
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,949
And I mean a come-to-Jesus talk.

321
00:15:40,089 --> 00:15:43,786
You're not my mother, Naomi.
You're not even my boss.

322
00:15:48,230 --> 00:15:51,358
Everybody's patience
is wearing thin, Dell.

323
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:58,238
- What?
- Hey, Naomi won't push this, I will.

324
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:00,137
Leave. Take the day.

325
00:16:00,275 --> 00:16:02,266
Get it together, Dell.

326
00:16:05,481 --> 00:16:10,475
I'd just found out about Bill's affair.
From his e-mail.

327
00:16:10,886 --> 00:16:12,854
There were lots of e-mails
from different women.

328
00:16:12,988 --> 00:16:15,252
Pictures.

329
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:17,291
They were all so young.

330
00:16:18,827 --> 00:16:21,819
And I was feeling old and insecure.

331
00:16:21,964 --> 00:16:25,593
- And Bobby?
- He just got transferred into my class.

332
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:28,362
The way he looked at me, it just...

333
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:31,005
It just made me feel better.

334
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:34,439
He'd find reasons to stay after
and I'd help him with his homework.

335
00:16:34,576 --> 00:16:37,568
When we wanted a break,
we'd just start talking.

336
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,004
For hours.

337
00:16:40,149 --> 00:16:42,413
I tried to get him to focus
on girls his own age.

338
00:16:42,885 --> 00:16:44,546
He kept coming back to me.

339
00:16:44,687 --> 00:16:47,383
I know, but you're the adult.
You should have stopped him.

340
00:16:47,523 --> 00:16:49,354
I love him.

341
00:16:49,491 --> 00:16:51,186
Oh, look, I know it's wrong.

342
00:16:51,326 --> 00:16:53,920
But when I thought something
was gonna happen to him in the...

343
00:16:54,063 --> 00:16:56,896
This is a crime,
and we should be reporting it.

344
00:16:57,032 --> 00:16:59,193
SAM: Yeah, bottom line,
you can't see him anymore.

345
00:16:59,334 --> 00:17:01,234
- If you do...
- Yeah, don't.

346
00:17:04,073 --> 00:17:05,700
Okay.

347
00:17:14,883 --> 00:17:16,783
[NOAH SIGHS]

348
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:23,056
I hate heart transplants.

349
00:17:23,592 --> 00:17:25,423
You're basically waiting
for someone to die

350
00:17:25,561 --> 00:17:27,085
to save the person who you wanna live.

351
00:17:27,229 --> 00:17:31,427
It's horrible
to have to sit and wait and sit.

352
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:34,127
And not be in control.

353
00:17:34,269 --> 00:17:36,760
Well, you can only do so much.

354
00:17:37,439 --> 00:17:39,634
And if you've got a baby?

355
00:17:39,775 --> 00:17:43,176
A baby who could die,
you're content to just chalk it all up to fate?

356
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:46,076
No. Then it's on me.

357
00:17:46,215 --> 00:17:50,345
Exactly.
We are the ultimate narcissists.

358
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,113
Life and death is all up to us.

359
00:17:52,254 --> 00:17:56,156
No wonder so many doctors
are insufferable.

360
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,259
Am I?

361
00:17:59,795 --> 00:18:02,093
I think you're one of the good ones.

362
00:18:03,265 --> 00:18:05,631
[PAGERS BEEPING AND VIBRATING]

363
00:18:09,972 --> 00:18:13,738
When they brought him in,
I recognized him and I paged you.

364
00:18:13,876 --> 00:18:16,572
It's Phillip, Janine's husband.

365
00:18:21,617 --> 00:18:23,414
He's comatose. No corneal reflexes.

366
00:18:23,552 --> 00:18:25,850
- Type two diabetic. Tox screen negative.
- What happened?

367
00:18:25,988 --> 00:18:29,446
Glucose was initially less than ten.
Looks like an insulin overdose.

368
00:18:29,591 --> 00:18:31,855
EEG shows no evidence
of any brain activity.

369
00:18:31,994 --> 00:18:34,554
He's brain-dead.
Oh, my God, do you think...?

370
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:35,956
[ADDISON SIGHS]

371
00:18:36,098 --> 00:18:38,066
- What?
- He's an organ donor.

372
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,141
- Can I help you?
- I'm fine, thank you.

373
00:18:56,485 --> 00:18:59,249
I like the atmosphere.
Open, friendly, comfortable.

374
00:18:59,488 --> 00:19:02,184
Uh, what are you doing here?
I told you I was not interested.

375
00:19:02,324 --> 00:19:04,918
Well, I figured I'd check out exactly
what you're holding onto.

376
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:07,756
Well, that's not a very good idea, so...

377
00:19:07,896 --> 00:19:10,421
Because of the other Dr. Bennett?

378
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:11,794
I read his book. Don't worry.

379
00:19:11,934 --> 00:19:13,424
As far as he knows, I'm a patient.

380
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,696
I doubt he thinks
that I'm trying to get you pregnant.

381
00:19:15,838 --> 00:19:18,238
And you should go.

382
00:19:18,373 --> 00:19:20,238
Lunch tomorrow.

383
00:19:20,809 --> 00:19:22,106
You are pushing.

384
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:24,337
I'm a man who knows what he wants.

385
00:19:29,551 --> 00:19:31,075
Aren't you popular these days.

386
00:19:31,220 --> 00:19:32,482
What?

387
00:19:33,288 --> 00:19:35,722
- The guy you were just talking to.
- Oh, no.

388
00:19:35,858 --> 00:19:37,849
He's just... He's a patient, so...

389
00:19:37,993 --> 00:19:40,086
Good night, Sam.

390
00:19:40,229 --> 00:19:41,924
Good night.

391
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:46,299
I can't. I can't breathe.

392
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,902
I can't think.

393
00:19:48,337 --> 00:19:50,134
What am I gonna do without Phillip?

394
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:52,832
Janine, I know this is unthinkably hard.

395
00:19:52,975 --> 00:19:55,773
And none of us could possibly imagine.

396
00:19:55,911 --> 00:19:58,880
It's awful.
But I need you to focus right now.

397
00:19:59,014 --> 00:20:03,144
Focus on the baby that you're carrying,
the baby that you and Phillip created.

398
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:05,879
Because if you don't do this,
you both could die.

399
00:20:06,688 --> 00:20:11,591
My husband is dead and you want me
to take his heart to save myself?

400
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,858
- To save both of you.
- I can't.

401
00:20:14,997 --> 00:20:16,487
How could I?

402
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:19,396
Janine, listen to me.
It's hard for anyone to fathom.

403
00:20:19,534 --> 00:20:21,934
But the heart is a machine.

404
00:20:22,070 --> 00:20:24,937
A heart is tissue that provides
a hugely important function.

405
00:20:25,073 --> 00:20:26,904
It is not your husband.

406
00:20:27,042 --> 00:20:30,409
You are not taking from him.
He is providing for you.

407
00:20:30,545 --> 00:20:33,571
It's what he'd want, you know it is.

408
00:20:33,715 --> 00:20:37,242
Phillip's death is tragic,
but it's giving you a chance.

409
00:20:37,386 --> 00:20:40,150
Now you need to get over your fear
and do this.

410
00:20:40,289 --> 00:20:41,847
If not for you, for the baby.

411
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,855
And for you.

412
00:20:44,726 --> 00:20:46,921
He's my brother.

413
00:20:47,062 --> 00:20:48,962
And I haven't even digested that

414
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:55,001
because I know that there's
something more important right now.

415
00:20:55,570 --> 00:20:57,595
We can't save him.

416
00:20:58,307 --> 00:21:00,605
We can save you.

417
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:06,370
Once the heart's out,
we've got four to six hours to get it in.

418
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:08,210
Montgomery, Barnes, hold it.

419
00:21:08,717 --> 00:21:11,185
Don't you dare touch him.
You're not removing his heart.

420
00:21:16,792 --> 00:21:19,352
How is she? Donna?

421
00:21:19,494 --> 00:21:20,961
Um, I don't know.

422
00:21:21,096 --> 00:21:23,826
You know, we need to focus on you.
We're gonna get you better.

423
00:21:23,966 --> 00:21:26,560
I keep texting her. She won't answer.

424
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:28,829
I get it, Bobby.
People fall for their teachers.

425
00:21:28,971 --> 00:21:31,166
It wasn't like that.
I didn't have a crush on her.

426
00:21:31,306 --> 00:21:34,332
We started talking, and it was real.

427
00:21:35,577 --> 00:21:37,670
Have you ever talked to a teenage girl,
Dr. Freedman?

428
00:21:37,813 --> 00:21:41,010
It's like deciphering code.
This was a real conversation.

429
00:21:41,149 --> 00:21:42,548
Even so, given the age difference...

430
00:21:42,684 --> 00:21:45,676
Why are people so hung up on age?

431
00:21:45,821 --> 00:21:47,516
Donna.

432
00:21:47,656 --> 00:21:49,851
- You're not supposed to be here.
- I know, I just...

433
00:21:49,992 --> 00:21:52,051
- Donna.
- Hey, could you give us a minute?

434
00:21:52,194 --> 00:21:54,253
Um, no, I really can't.

435
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:55,920
- Please?
- We had a deal.

436
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:58,032
BOBBY:
I want you to go.

437
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:00,758
Mrs. Keating?

438
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:04,394
I just wanted to make sure
Bobby was feeling better.

439
00:22:05,140 --> 00:22:07,700
- Dr. Freedman, is there a problem?
- No, there's no problem.

440
00:22:07,843 --> 00:22:09,242
She's here to see me.

441
00:22:09,378 --> 00:22:12,347
I think you need to go, Donna, now.

442
00:22:13,715 --> 00:22:15,046
I never meant to hurt him.

443
00:22:15,183 --> 00:22:16,673
I don't understand.

444
00:22:16,818 --> 00:22:18,752
- I love her.
- You're sleeping with our son?

445
00:22:18,887 --> 00:22:20,252
Leave, now.

446
00:22:21,056 --> 00:22:22,990
- I'm sorry.
- Now.

447
00:22:29,431 --> 00:22:31,262
[CHUCKLING]

448
00:22:33,635 --> 00:22:34,932
[PETE SIGHS]

449
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:36,662
What?

450
00:22:38,874 --> 00:22:40,432
You know the woman
you met this morning?

451
00:22:40,575 --> 00:22:43,169
Violet, the pregnant woman.

452
00:22:43,311 --> 00:22:45,040
Yeah?

453
00:22:45,180 --> 00:22:47,148
We're not together.

454
00:22:48,383 --> 00:22:54,811
But there's a chance that it's my baby.

455
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:58,555
Look, I like you,

456
00:22:58,693 --> 00:23:00,991
and I wanna start things off being open.

457
00:23:01,596 --> 00:23:04,087
She doesn't know who the father is?

458
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,968
You know... Um...

459
00:23:07,402 --> 00:23:09,529
It's a long story.

460
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:12,940
What are you thinking?

461
00:23:13,075 --> 00:23:15,339
Do you know how hard it is
for a single mom to find a man

462
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:19,914
who's smart and funny and likes kids?

463
00:23:20,682 --> 00:23:26,348
Someone who likes me and my son,
who doesn't just think he's in the way?

464
00:23:33,195 --> 00:23:34,492
I like you, Pete.

465
00:23:34,963 --> 00:23:37,659
This feels good and right.

466
00:23:37,799 --> 00:23:40,199
So it's not the end of the world.

467
00:23:42,104 --> 00:23:45,938
But I have Ben,
and I have to protect him.

468
00:23:46,074 --> 00:23:51,205
So I guess what I really need to know is,
what are you thinking?

469
00:23:56,751 --> 00:23:58,218
Where's your head at, Montgomery?

470
00:23:58,353 --> 00:23:59,820
Woman needs a heart, can't find one.

471
00:23:59,955 --> 00:24:02,048
Suddenly her husband drops dead,
bam, you got one.

472
00:24:02,190 --> 00:24:04,681
- Awfully convenient.
- Yes, it's very coincidental, Charlotte.

473
00:24:04,826 --> 00:24:07,989
And perhaps we could ponder
just how coincidental it is if we had time.

474
00:24:08,130 --> 00:24:10,360
- But we don't.
- His wife is deteriorating.

475
00:24:10,499 --> 00:24:13,059
She needs that heart now.
If we wait, she'll die.

476
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:16,231
Insulin overdose is a well-known cause
of death in diabetics.

477
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:18,430
Accidental overdose or on purpose?

478
00:24:18,573 --> 00:24:21,667
Because this hospital will not condone
suicide to provide organs.

479
00:24:21,810 --> 00:24:25,041
Or be party to destroying evidence
if it wasn't an accident.

480
00:24:25,180 --> 00:24:28,343
I want someone from the ME's office
to collect trace evidence from the body

481
00:24:28,483 --> 00:24:29,643
and find me a cause of death.

482
00:24:29,784 --> 00:24:30,978
Before you touch him.

483
00:24:31,119 --> 00:24:32,814
If he was murdered,
we destroy evidence...

484
00:24:32,954 --> 00:24:35,184
- We don't have time, Charlotte.
