00:37:50,651 --> 00:37:54,052
No, I'm sorry.

729
00:38:01,762 --> 00:38:03,286
Bobby, I know that you love her.

730
00:38:03,431 --> 00:38:08,368
But sometimes the best thing to do
when you love someone and it's not right

731
00:38:09,603 --> 00:38:12,800
is to just let go and move on.

732
00:38:24,785 --> 00:38:27,049
- Charlotte.
- William.

733
00:38:27,188 --> 00:38:30,316
- I had no idea you were in town.
- Just a bit of business.

734
00:38:30,458 --> 00:38:34,087
I wanted to check in and see
how my practice was doing.

735
00:38:34,895 --> 00:38:35,953
There were some bumps,

736
00:38:36,097 --> 00:38:39,464
but I'm feeling good
about where things are heading.

737
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:41,864
Patient bookings are strong.

738
00:38:42,003 --> 00:38:44,995
Good, good. I'm glad to hear it.

739
00:38:47,108 --> 00:38:49,872
That's all you wanted?

740
00:38:50,011 --> 00:38:53,674
I'll be back in a couple weeks. You can
bring me up to speed on everything then.

741
00:39:05,292 --> 00:39:07,157
You were right.

742
00:39:07,294 --> 00:39:13,324
I wasn't being honest.
And I think maybe I should be.

743
00:39:16,003 --> 00:39:17,334
You know what I think?

744
00:39:17,471 --> 00:39:22,170
I think that what we're doing is too hard.

745
00:39:22,877 --> 00:39:26,711
We're divorced,
but I still care about you.

746
00:39:26,847 --> 00:39:31,875
And hearing about everybody you're dating
and what you're doing, it's just...

747
00:39:32,019 --> 00:39:34,112
It's not good, for either of us.

748
00:39:34,255 --> 00:39:36,780
You said you could handle it.
I mean, I thought we were friends.

749
00:39:36,924 --> 00:39:41,224
I know I did, and we are. But I...

750
00:39:41,362 --> 00:39:44,525
When your dating pool
is everybody that I know,

751
00:39:44,665 --> 00:39:48,601
Archer, Bryce, Duncan,
there's a limit, Nai.

752
00:39:49,203 --> 00:39:53,833
And maybe I said I could handle it,
but I can't and I shouldn't have to.

753
00:39:56,410 --> 00:39:59,436
- So, what are you saying?
- We can't be friends anymore.

754
00:40:00,347 --> 00:40:01,905
I need some distance.

755
00:40:02,049 --> 00:40:04,984
To let go. To move on.

756
00:40:07,188 --> 00:40:10,123
- You want distance.
- I need it.

757
00:40:12,693 --> 00:40:14,354
Don't you?

758
00:40:15,529 --> 00:40:17,588
- Yeah.
- Okay.

759
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:33,143
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

760
00:40:56,170 --> 00:40:57,535
Pete.

761
00:41:02,276 --> 00:41:03,834
Oh, Sheldon, what happened?

762
00:41:03,978 --> 00:41:05,741
Anita thought
I was gonna confess my love.

763
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:09,543
When I insisted her feelings were
misplaced, she beat me with the roses.

764
00:41:09,683 --> 00:41:11,150
- It was great.
- It was great?

765
00:41:11,285 --> 00:41:14,345
I forced her.
I pushed her to a breakthrough, Violet.

766
00:41:14,488 --> 00:41:17,048
And when she saw what she did to me,
she broke down.

767
00:41:17,191 --> 00:41:20,319
She realized she'd spent so much money
on gifts for the wrong person.

768
00:41:20,461 --> 00:41:23,919
She called her co-worker from the office,
and they're having dinner.

769
00:41:24,064 --> 00:41:27,397
Wow. You should feel so proud,
Sheldon.

770
00:41:28,002 --> 00:41:30,232
You know,
you gotta put something on that.

771
00:41:30,371 --> 00:41:33,772
But that's not the best part. The best part
is I had a breakthrough of my own.

772
00:41:33,908 --> 00:41:36,433
When someone has feelings
and doesn't let the other person know,

773
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:38,670
that's a missed opportunity.

774
00:41:38,812 --> 00:41:40,336
But isn't that what I said before?

775
00:41:40,481 --> 00:41:45,851
Yes. And I convinced Anita,
but then I realized that it applied to me.

776
00:41:45,986 --> 00:41:48,045
I'm in love with you, Violet.

777
00:41:48,189 --> 00:41:51,488
From the first time we rode
on that elevator.

778
00:41:51,625 --> 00:41:53,957
I don't care whose child you're carrying.

779
00:41:54,528 --> 00:41:57,759
I can talk to you about anything.
I wanna talk to you about everything.

780
00:41:57,898 --> 00:42:02,494
And when I'm not with you, I'm empty.

781
00:42:04,905 --> 00:42:06,634
Will you marry me?
